## 📌 Project Overview
A console-based ATM Interface built in Java using
Object-Oriented Programming principles.
Two separate classes handle UI and business logic cleanly.

## ✨ Features
| # | Feature | Details |
|---|---------|---------|
| 1 | 💰 Check Balance | Displays account info and current balance |
| 2 | ➕ Deposit | Validates and adds money to account |
| 3 | ➖ Withdraw | Validates amount and checks sufficient funds |
| 4 | 🔒 Encapsulation | Balance is private — protected from direct access |
| 5 | 🛡 Input Validation | Never crashes on bad input using hasNextDouble() |
| 6 | 🏗 Separated Logic | ATM class (UI) separate from BankAccount class (Logic) |

## 🧠 Java Concepts Used
| Concept | Where Used |
|---------|-----------|
| Classes & Objects | BankAccount and ATM are separate classes |
| Encapsulation | private balance with public getters/setters |
| Methods | deposit(), withdraw(), checkBalance() |
| Constructor | BankAccount initialized with account details |
| Input Validation | hasNextDouble(), hasNextInt() |
| While Loop | Main ATM run loop + input validation loop |
| Switch Statement | Menu choice handling |

## 🚀 How to Run
**Step 1 — Compile**
```bash
javac ATMInterface.java
```
**Step 2 — Run**
```bash
java ATMInterface
```

